- Rainfall anomaly is when the rainfall deviates significantly from the average or expected rainfall in a particular region; 
- NDVI is a measure of vegetation health; 
- Model performance metrics (r2_train, r2_val, loss_to_minimize) indicate how accurately a model can predict climate anomalies; 
- Access patterns can indicate user interest or needs for climate data.

- High R-squared values (r2_val > 0.7) typically indicate a good fit between the model and data; 
- Low loss values (loss_to_minimize < 0.5) suggest the model is well-optimized;
- A large region area (area_km2 > 10000) could imply a diverse or complex climate.
